During the First World War, the Italian army built a comprehensive system of the third defense line at Kolovrat, a part of which is now arranged in an outdoor museum. There are command and observation posts, machine guns and artillery positions, caverns and a network of ditches. The visit to this location is especially interesting because of various details, such as a stingy staircase in one of the caverns and to a great extent the original materials used during the war. Museum Kolovrat is a cross-border museum, which continues on the Italian side.
